player.seasonOutlook: Waller retired after eight seasons with the Ravens, Raiders and Giants. His lone season season with the Giants was not successful, as he missed at least five games with an injury for the third consecutive season, and his on-field production when he did play was muted. Waller averaged 9.4 fantasy points in his 12 games, not far from top-10 production, but nothing like his fabulous 2019 and 2020 campaigns. Even if he changes course and decides to return, Waller is no longer a fantasy starter.
